description:
A day like any other Friday, only an all-out-race war is underway today and no one in this upscale neighborhood is safe, not even a young child whose purity and innocence serves as counterpoint to the chaotic turmoil unfolding all around him.

Rolf Forsberg's critically acclaimed, controversial Parable was the main attraction at the Protestant and Orthodox Pavilion of the 1964 New York World's Fair. A mysterious clown in all white attire appears as a Christ-like figure to redeem a circus. Also includes three other fllms by Rolf Forsberg, The Antkeeper, The Ark, and One Friday plus interviews with Rolf.

Director: Rolf Forsberg, Tom Rook
Starring: Clarence Mitchell, Jack Gwynne
